        "title": "Oatmeal Cookies",
        "excerpt":"Oatmeal cookies are a proverbial favorite with both kids and adults. This crisp and chewy cookie is loaded with oats, dried fruit, and chopped nuts.   Ingredients      1 cup butter, softened 1 cup white sugar   1 cup packed brown sugar   2 eggs   1 teaspoon vanilla extract   2 cups all-purpose flour   1 teaspoon baking soda   1 teaspoon salt   1 1/2 teaspoons ground cinnamon   3 cups quick cooking oats   Directions      In a medium bowl, cream together butter, white sugar, and brown sugar. Beat in eggs one at a time, then stir in vanilla. Combine flour, baking soda, salt, and cinnamon; stir into the creamed mixture. Mix in oats. Cover, and chill dough for at least one hour.   Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Grease cookie sheets. Roll the dough into walnut sized balls, and place 2 inches apart on cookie sheets. Flatten each cookie with a large fork dipped in sugar.   Bake for 8 to 10 minutes in preheated oven. Allow cookies to cool on baking sheet for 5 minutes before transferring to a wire rack to cool completely.  ","categories": ["Recept"],
